[mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the PyPI (Python Package Index) page for "types-aiobotocore-devops-guru" version 2.12.1, released on March 5, 2024. It provides type annotations for the aiobotocore.DevOpsGuru service, compatible with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, and mypy. The package, developed by Vlad Emelianov, requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. It supports a wide range of Python versions from 3.8 to 3.13 and is designed to be OS independent. The package aims to enhance code completion and error detection by providing explicit type annotations for aiobotocore services, making it easier for developers to work with AWS DevOps Guru services in an asynchronous manner. Installation instructions, usage examples, and information on how to contribute or report issues are also provided.
